                        <div class="entry-content">
                            <p>We have seen the graph of total cases many times. Of course the main focus has been
                                China, US, Italy and Spain, but the question that everyone has is how my country doing
                                regarding the infection rate, the percentage of new cases versus one day before and the
                                death rate. There are plenty of questions, that make us doubt about the data, if each
                                country is doing the same amount of testing, if the cases are being register on time or
                                not, but for now this is the only data we have. I have put Italy and Spain as reference
                                because we have seen that these two countries have been hit very hard with the
                                Coronavirus crisis. I am glad that Poland rate seems much lower than these countries and
                                it seems that the early adoptions of the quarantine are showing results. The result on
                                Mexico even do are doubtful, due to the limit amount of testing that is being done,
                                shows good results. I hope they are really good and is not that the government that has
                                decided to hide information from the people.
                            </p>
                            </br>
                            <p>Note: This graph is updated daily so my comments might not be accurate at
                                the time you see the graph.</p>

