                            <h3 class="text-brand">#Zostanwdomu Poland</h3>

                            <p>Google has updated his COVID19 mobility reports on the 9th of April. Poland people are
                                starting to go more for Retail and recreation. The past report was showing a reduction
                                of 78% compared to baseline, the current report now shows 71%. That means there was a 7%
                                more people going outside for these activities. Grocery visits show a very interesting
                                report because last reports show a decrease of 59% but now, we are seeing an increase of
                                41% probably related to Eastern celebration in Poland. Workplace are also showing an
                                increase on mobility, last report shows a reduction of 36% compared to baseline and the
                                current report now shows a 27% reduction. This means more people are going to their
                                workplace compared than before. In the next weeks the activity in Europe will be
                                increasing in workplaces let’s hope the amount of cases and deaths doesn’t increases as
                                much.
                            </p>
                            <img class="post-img img-responsive text-center" src="assets/images/polandgoogle1.jpg"
                                alt="">
                            <img class="post-img img-responsive text-center" src="assets/images/polandgoogle2.jpg"
                                alt="">
                            <h4 class="text-brand">Death Rate Poland</h4>
                            <div id="graficaPolonia"></div>
                            <p>The below graphs are an idea I saw on the Financial Times. These are two graph, new cases
                                and new deaths with a 7-day rolling average, the idea behind these graphs is that these
                                will help to see if we have reach the top of the curve or not. So far what I can see is
                                that the new cases graph in Poland seems to reach the plateau at around 430 new cases
                                per day. Hopefully in the next days, with more work centers operating normal now that
                                the lockdown will be reduce on many countries in Europe we don’t see an increase on this
                                graph. On the second graph on the new deaths per day, that is still not showing signs
                                that we have reach a top. It still seems a growing graph with around 20 new deaths per
                                day. </p>
                            <h4 class="text-brand">New Cases Poland per Day (7-day Rolling Average)</h4>
